  "text": "To standardize for observation time and estimate the average number of species observed at a site, we used rarefaction curves [CITATION_1] ) (with observation time on the x-axis and species richness observed on the y-axis). For 6.3 person-hours, the average observation time at a site, on average 31 species were observed in fallow ®elds vs. 18 species in active pastures, and this difference was signi®cant at the 0.05 level (the 95% con®dence intervals did not cross). There was no signi®cant difference between the number of species observed in fallow ®elds and coffee plots.",
